<div id="content" lang="en" dir="ltr">
2.3.0, rolled up a Dunédán Sorceror, small/ironman, worshipping Melkor. Killed 2 thieves in Bree and got SIX (6) skill points to allocate... <p>
Email me (<a href="http://web.archive.org/web/20041020134230/mailto:kalon9999@hotmail.com">kalon9999@hotmail.com</a>) if you want a coppy of my save folder (Windows). 
</p>
<p>
<strong><a href="./MayLith">MayLith</a></strong>: Uhhhhh.... I may be misremembering but I believe that is normal game behavior for 2.3.0. 
</p>
<p>
<strong><a href="./NeilStevens">NeilStevens</a></strong>: Yes, it is correct.  I'm pretty sure it's even documented in changes.txt. 
</p>
<p>
<strong><a href="./SoulWynd">SoulWynd</a></strong>: Yeah, but nobody really pays attention to those. I gotta make a module with 1000 skill points per level &gt;.&gt; 
</p>
<p>
Dryad: then how come I get 5 per level? What is the intended behavior anyway? 
</p>
<p>
<strong><a href="./FearofFours">FearofFours</a></strong>: Dryad, you should receive 5 skill points if you are playing version 2.2.7 or earlier, but 6 skill points if you are play(testing) pre-release 2.3.0.  
</p>
